## 8 · WORKTREES

### 8.1 — Parallel Feature Development

```
Create isolated worktrees for parallel feature development:
1. wt-add feat-[name-1] — [module 1]
2. wt-add feat-[name-2] — [module 2]
3. wt-add feat-[name-3] — [module 3]

Assign one coder agent per worktree. Each gets its own PG Vector schema namespace.
All agents share the same Beads database. Each agent claims tasks with bd update <id> --claim.

After all complete:
- Run gnx-analyze on each to check blast radius
- Review conflicts before merging
- wt-clean to remove all worktrees
```

### 8.2 — Hotfix Worktree

```
Create a worktree for an emergency hotfix:
1. wt-add hotfix-[issue-number]
2. Branch from the production tag
3. Fix the issue with minimal changes
4. Run aqe-gate for quality checks
5. Create PR, get review, merge
6. wt-remove hotfix-[issue-number]
7. bd create "Hotfix: [description]" -t bug -p 0
```

### 8.3 — Multi-Agent Worktree with Shared Beads

```
Set up a multi-agent development environment:
1. bd init
2. bd dolt set mode server && bd dolt start
3. Create worktrees:
   wt-add agent-architect
   wt-add agent-coder-1
   wt-add agent-coder-2
   wt-add agent-tester
4. Each agent claims work: bd update <task-id> --claim --assignee agent-coder-1
5. Agents track progress: bd update <task-id> --comment "Implemented auth, tests passing"
6. When done: bd close <task-id> --reason "Completed: [summary]"
7. Cleanup: bd dolt stop && wt-clean
```

